# <type>(<scope>): <description>    ← subject (imperative, max 72 chars)
#
# [optional body]                   ← explain WHAT and WHY (wrap at 72)
#
# [optional footer]                 ← Closes #123, BREAKING CHANGE:
#
# ── Types ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# feat:     ✨ New feature
# fix:      🐛 Bug fix
# docs:     📚 Documentation only
# style:    💄 Formatting (no code change)
# refactor: ♻️  Code restructuring (no feat/fix)
# test:     🧪 Adding/updating tests
# chore:    🔧 Maintenance, tooling
# ci:       🔄 CI/CD changes
# perf:     ⚡ Performance improvement
# build:    📦 Build system changes
# revert:   ⏪ Revert a previous commit
# release:  🚀 Release / version bump
#
# ── Rules ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# • Subject: imperative mood ("add" not "added")
# • Subject: no period at end
# • Subject: max 72 characters
# • Body: blank line between subject and body
# • Body: wrap at 72 characters
# • Footer: reference issues (Closes #42)
# • Footer: BREAKING CHANGE: description
#
# ── Examples ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# feat(auth): add OAuth2 login support
#
# fix(api): handle null response in user endpoint
#
# Closes #42
#
# release: v2.0.0
#
# chore!: drop Node.js 16 support
#
# BREAKING CHANGE: Minimum Node.js version is now 18.
